Figure Tag Lab

In this lab, you have to create a figure element with an image and a caption.
The figure attribute is used to visually group different elements together as a single unit.

Images, illustrations, graphs, or any other visual content can be placed inside a figure element.
The figcaption element represents a caption or a legend associated with a figure.

Challenges:

1. Create a figure element with the attribute id set to 'myFigure'.
2. Add an image img to the figure with id set to 'figureImage' and set src any online image of your choice
3. Add a figcaption element to the figure with the id set to 'myCaption' and set the text of the figcaption of your choice
4. Create a CSS rule to set the font style of '#myCaption' to italic.
